# Queen Marika the Eternal · the god of the Golden Order, who shattered the Ring

Queen Marika the Eternal is the god of the Golden Order — the chosen vessel of the Greater Will. It was she who raised the Erdtree's Order, she who removed Destined Death from the Elden Ring, and she who reigned eternal in Leyndell. The Order's gold flows from her godhood; the world the game inherits is the world she ordained.

She is also Radagon, her own other half — one being, two selves, a mystery seated at the very heart of the Order. The Golden Order's deepest riddle is not beneath her; it is her.

Then came the Night of the Black Knives, which killed the soul of her son Godwyn. After that loss, Marika shattered the Elden Ring with her own hand — god turned rebel against her own god — and for it she was imprisoned, broken, within the Erdtree. The Eternal Queen is god, rebel, and the wound the whole game inherits: the breaking traces back to her own hand.

Her emergence is spiritual because she is godhood itself within the Order — the divine made sovereign. The Golden Order's heart is her mystery; even her rebellion was an act of a god against her own god, a wound dealt in the register of the divine.
